\{w_1,...,w_n\}
(X, \|\cdot\|)
D:= \{ \sum_{i=1}^n \alpha_iw_i : \alpha_i \in \mathbb{Q} \ \ \ \forall 1 \leq i \leq n\}.
D
\mathbb{Q}^n
D
x \in X
\epsilon > 0
\lambda_1,...\lambda_n \in \mathbb{R}
x =\sum_{i=1}^n \lambda_iw_i
1 \leq i \leq n
\alpha_i \in \mathbb{Q}
|\alpha_i - \lambda_i| < \epsilon/nK
K:= \max\{\|w_i\| : 1 \leq i \leq n\}.
y:= \sum_{i=1}^n \alpha_iw_i \in D
\|x - y \| \leq \sum_{i=1}^n|\alpha_i - \lambda_i|\cdot \|w_i\| < nK \frac{\epsilon}{nK}   = \epsilon .
